def: A disavowing or disowning. Bp. Hall.
The state of being enravished or enraptured; ecstasy; rapture.Glanvill.
To traffic or trade, by exchanging one commodity for another,in distinction from a sale and purchase, in which money is paid forthe commodities transferred; to truck.
To conquer again; to recover by conquest; as, to reconquer arevolted province.
Not medullated; (Anat.) without a medulla or marrow, or withouta medullary sheath; as, a nonmedullated nerve fiber.
Having a conspicious tongue; -- said of certain reptiles andinsects.
A ball or globe forming part of the regalia of an emperor orother sovereign. It is encircled with bands, enriched with preciousstones, and surmounted with a cross; -- called also globe.
Capable of being reconverted; convertible again to the originalform or condition.
